# docstats

## Build & Test
- `gh auth switch --user ringo380` — required before any `gh` commands (two accounts; ringo380 owns this repo)
- `pip install -e ".[web]"` / `pip install -e ".[dev]"`
- `pytest` · `ruff check .` · `ruff format --check .` · `mypy src/docstats/` (all CI-gated)
- `docstats web` — start web UI at http://127.0.0.1:8000

## Architecture

### Module layout
- `src/docstats/` — one module per concern, each <300 lines. Core (client, models, storage, cache, normalize, scoring) has zero Rich/Typer/FastAPI deps.
- Web routes split into `routes/` subpackage (see directory listing). Shared helpers in `routes/_common.py`; shared rate-limit decorator in `routes/_rate_limit.py`. `web.py` is app shell only (middleware, exception handlers, router includes, home/history).
- `services.py` — sync CLI-only service layer (search + save with scoring + history). Web routes have their own async paths.
- `domain/` — referral-platform domain layer. Keep FastAPI-free where possible; FastAPI deps live in `routes/`.

### Storage: dual-backend
- Supabase Postgres in prod (when `SUPABASE_URL` + `SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY` set), SQLite fallback for local/CLI. Supabase tables use `docstats_` prefix (shared project ref `uhnymifvdauzlmaogjfj`).
- `StorageBase` ABC in `storage_base.py` + shared helpers (`normalize_email`, `fuzzy_score`). `storage.py` = SQLite; `pg_storage.py` = Supabase. `get_storage()` returns the right one.
- SQLite DB at `~/.local/share/docstats/docstats.db`. Connections require `PRAGMA journal_mode=WAL` + `PRAGMA foreign_keys=ON` + `check_same_thread=False`.
- Pg `_row_to_*` helpers must route timestamps through `_parse_sqlite_utc` (SQLite side) so comparisons are tz-aware UTC like Supabase.
- No auto-migration for Postgres. Add columns via Management API SQL before deploying referencing code. Migration files: `docs/migrations/NNN_name.sql`. Apply: `curl -sS -X POST "https://api.supabase.com/v1/projects/uhnymifvdauzlmaogjfj/database/query" -H "Authorization: Bearer $SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN" -H "Content-Type: application/json" --data "$(jq -Rs '{query: .}' file.sql)"`. Python `urllib.request` hits Cloudflare 403 — use curl.

### Scope / multi-tenancy
- `scope.py`: `Scope(user_id, organization_id, membership_role)` + `scope_sql_clause(scope, user_col=..., org_col=...) -> (fragment, params)` + `ScopeRequired`. Anonymous = all None; solo = user_id only; org = both + role. `routes._common.get_scope` resolves from session + memberships; silently falls back to solo if `active_org_id` stale.
- Phase-1+ scope-owned rows (patients, referrals, attachments, insurance_plans, csv_imports) carry exactly one of `scope_user_id` / `scope_organization_id` — CHECK constraint at DB level + two filter helpers: `scope_sql_clause(scope)` for raw SQLite SQL; `PostgresStorage._apply_scope(query, scope)` wraps supabase-py chains. Both raise `ScopeRequired` on anon. `_require_scoped(scope)` is the Postgres choke-point for inserts.
- Sub-entities (referral_diagnoses/medications/allergies/attachments, referral_events, referral_responses, csv_import_rows) are scope-transitive — no scope columns; parent-referral/import scope-gate on every method.
- Reference data has two shapes: `insurance_plans` is scope-owned like patients; `specialty_rules` + `payer_rules` use nullable `organization_id` where NULL=platform default, int=org override. Partial unique indices keep one global per code + one override per (org, code).

### Patients & referrals
- Patients (1.A): `domain/patients.py`. MRN unique within org via partial unique index `WHERE deleted_at IS NULL` so soft-delete frees MRN. `update_patient` skips fields where caller passed None (None means "leave alone"); clearing goes through `clear_*_field` allow-listed routes.
- Referrals (1.B): `domain/referrals.py` — `Referral`, `ReferralEvent`, enum vocabularies, `STATUS_TRANSITIONS` + `transition_allowed()` / `require_transition()`. Storage: create/get/list (filter by patient/status/assignee/urgency natively), update, `set_referral_status` (no transition check — caller validates via `require_transition`), soft_delete, `clear_referral_field` (4-name allow-list: assigned_to_user_id, authorization_number, payer_plan_id, external_reference_id — ICD/text intentionally NOT clearable since denormalized), append-only `record_referral_event`/`list_referral_events`.
- Cross-scope `patient_id` / `payer_plan_id` on create/update raises `ValueError`. `created` event auto-seeded on insert (SQLite: single `with self._conn:` tx; Postgres: compensating soft-delete on event-insert failure). Event shape invariant: `from_value` = OLD, `to_value` = NEW, `note` = field name or free text.
- Patient FK on referral: `ON DELETE RESTRICT` (referrals are evidence). Contrast: `saved_providers.user_id` is `CASCADE` (per-user rolodex).
- Clinical sub-tables (1.C): 4× tables hang off `referrals(id)` with `ON DELETE CASCADE`. Hard-delete (not soft) — `referral_events` captures edits. Every row has `source` from `SOURCE_VALUES`. One primary diagnosis enforced via partial unique on `is_primary`. Headline sync: `_sync_referral_primary_diagnosis` writes `referrals.diagnosis_primary_icd`/`text`; caller owns tx boundary (SQLite wraps sub-write + sync in one `with self._conn:`; Postgres has small atomicity gap).
- Responses (1.D): `referral_responses` — closed-loop from receiving side. Multiple per referral allowed. `consult_completed=True` is the signal for the route layer to transition parent to `completed` (storage doesn't cascade).
- Enum CHECK constraints must match Python vocabularies — `test_all_*_values_pass_*` tests catch drift.

### Rules engine (Phase 3)
- `domain/rules.py`: `resolve_specialty_rule(storage, org_id, code)` / `resolve_payer_rule(storage, org_id, InsurancePlan)` fetch ≤2 rows (global + any override) via storage-level `specialty_code=` / `payer_key=` narrowing. Last row in the ordered result wins (org override sorts after global via `nullsfirst=True`).
- `evaluate(referral, ruleset)` → `CompletenessReportV2` (parallel to baseline `CompletenessReport`, not a subclass). Specialty-required fields promote existing recommended baseline items via `_FIELD_TO_BASELINE_CODE`. Required-field satisfaction intersects baseline with a specialty-specific `_check_referral_field` call — baseline is often more permissive than the admin's actual requirement (e.g. baseline `primary_diagnosis` satisfied by ICD OR free-text; specialty might require the ICD).
- Red flags: `detect_red_flags_in_text(reason, clinical_question, specialty)` (text-first) + `detect_red_flags(referral, specialty)` wrapper. `referral_create` auto-escalates `routine` → `urgent` on red-flag hit; higher user-picked urgencies are never overridden. Auto-escalations emit `field_edited` event with `note="urgency (auto-escalated: red flags [...])"`.
- Payer key derivation: `payer_name|plan_type`. `create_insurance_plan` rejects `|` in `payer_name` with `ValueError` so the derived key stays unambiguous.
- Boot-time seeding: `web.py` lifespan calls `seed_platform_defaults(storage)` (12 specialties + 8 payers). Failure non-fatal (logs + continues). CLI: `docstats seed-rules [--overwrite]`. `DOCSTATS_SKIP_BOOT_SEED=1` disables (conftest sets by default). Lifespan fires BEFORE request DI so tests must `monkeypatch.setattr(docstats.web, "seed_platform_defaults", fake)` — dep-overrides don't hit the lifespan.

### CSV imports (Phase 4)
- `csv_imports` scope-owned; `csv_import_rows` scope-transitive, CASCADE on parent, unique `(import_id, row_index)`. Both hard-delete (ephemeral staging, not evidence). `csv_import_rows.referral_id` FK uses `ON DELETE SET NULL` so deleting a created referral doesn't wipe import provenance. Cross-scope referral_id on row update raises `ValueError`.
- State machines: `IMPORT_STATUS_VALUES` (uploaded→mapped→validated→committed, `failed` terminal) + `IMPORT_ROW_STATUS_VALUES`. `require_import_transition` / `require_row_transition` — route validates, storage is dumb.
- `routes/imports.py`: parse once at upload, persist verbatim cells to `csv_import_rows.raw_json`, re-read per step (no disk/blob needed). Caps: 5MB / 2000 rows (utf-8-sig). `TARGET_FIELD_GROUPS` + `_TARGET_ALIASES` drive auto-match. Mapping stored as `{target: csv_header}` (inverse of form). Save auto-runs validation. Row-level validators in `domain/imports_validate.py` (framework-free) with `specialty_cache` kwarg. Inline edit only modifies existing keys. Commit writes to live tables with `external_source="bulk_csv"`; per-row failures go in `validation_errors["commit"]` and don't abort batch. `/imports/template.csv` unauthenticated (public contract).
- `_upsert_patient_from_row` returns `(entity, was_created)` tuples; compensating soft-delete on failure (Postgres REST has no multi-statement transaction).

### Export pipeline (Phase 5)
- `src/docstats/exports/pdf.py` FastAPI-free; 7 artifact constants + `render_*` fns returning PDF bytes. `render_packet` uses `pypdf` to concat. Templates: `templates/exports/*.html`; shared CSS: `static/print.css` (Letter page, counters, urgency chips).
- `routes/exports.py` dispatches via `_ARTIFACT_BUNDLES: dict[artifact, (fetcher, renderer, filename_stem, display_label)]` — one tuple append per new artifact. `GET /referrals/{id}/export.pdf?artifact=<name>` streams PDF (PHI-gated, scope-enforced, WeasyPrint in executor). Audits `referral.export` + emits `record_referral_event(event_type="exported")`.
- Filenames server-controlled `referral-{id}-{stem}.pdf` (no PHI). Headers: `Content-Disposition: inline`, `Cache-Control: private, no-store`, `X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff`.
- Packet default include order: `fax_cover, summary, attachments`. `?include` capped `max_length=256`. Nested packet (`include=packet`) → 400. Audit metadata shape: `artifact: "packet:<csv-include>"`.
- FHIR (5.D): `exports/fhir.py` pure-Python. `build_referral_bundle(referral, patient, ...)` → R4 Bundle type=document. "FHIR-ish" — not guaranteed to pass strict validator. Status map pinned by `test_build_referral_bundle_status_map` — new `STATUS_VALUES` entry must also land in `_STATUS_MAP`.
- Workspace exports (5.E): `GET /referrals/export.csv` (cap 2000, same filter vocab) + `POST /referrals/batch-export.pdf` (cap 50; `referral_ids` as comma-separated `str` — `list[int] = Form()` parsing is broken; skipped IDs in `X-Export-Skipped` header + audit). Literal CSV + batch routes MUST precede `/{referral_id}/...` in the router (FastAPI matches declaration order; `{referral_id: int}` would try to coerce `"export.csv"` to int).
- Mapping source-of-truth: `docs/fhir-mapping.md`. API contract: `docs/api-v2.md`. Runbooks: `docs/delivery.md`, `docs/attachments.md`, `docs/csv-import-schema.md`.
- WeasyPrint system deps via Railway `railpack.json` (BOTH `buildAptPackages` + `deploy.aptPackages`): `libpango-1.0-0 libpangoft2-1.0-0 libharfbuzz0b libcairo2`. Local macOS: `brew install pango cairo`. Tests use `pytest.importorskip("weasyprint", ...)`.

### Admin console (Phase 6)
- `routes/admin.py` + `routes/admin_deliveries.py`. `require_admin_scope` is the single gate — `scope.is_org AND has_role_at_least(scope.membership_role, "admin")`. Sub-admins → 403; anonymous → 303 via `AuthRequiredException`. Don't re-check roles in handlers.
- `get_current_user` computes `user["is_org_admin"]` via one extra DB round-trip when `active_org_id` set; lookup failures fail-closed (nav hidden).
- Specialty rules editor (6.B): `overwrite=True` on save (empty display_name should clear, not be skipped). Unknown `required_field` checkbox names filtered against `REQUIRED_FIELD_CHECKS` vocabulary. `recommended_attachments.kinds` preserved verbatim (admin UI doesn't expose it). Revert hard-deletes override; idempotent no-ops don't audit. Redirect discipline: every mutating admin handler exits via `_redirect_after_save(request, dest)` (returns `HX-Redirect` for htmx, `303 Location` otherwise). Never inline `Response(status_code=303)` — htmx doesn't follow 3xx.
- Payer rules (6.C): same pattern. Keys URL-encoded (`|` in payer_key) via Jinja `| urlencode` + `urllib.parse.quote(k, safe='')` in tests. `POST /revert` declared before `POST /{payer_key}` for route-ordering safety.
- Org settings (6.D): scope-owned; no path param. `update_organization(overwrite=True)` raises if `name` is None/empty (NOT NULL). Route validates `name`/`npi`/`address_state` (US_STATES)/`address_zip` (`^\d{5}(?:-?\d{4})?$`). Slug intentionally immutable.
- Audit log viewer (6.E): paginated (50/page, offset-cap 10000, fetch `page_size+1` for has-next). Filters: action / entity_type / entity_id / actor_user_id / since (inclusive) / until (advanced by 1 day so admin's range is inclusive both ends, storage treats exclusive). `_KNOWN_AUDIT_ACTIONS` seeds datalist; free-text input. `list_audit_events` gained `action`/`since`/`until`/`offset`. supabase-py `.range(start, end)` inclusive zero-indexed — use `.limit()` when offset is zero.
- Members + invitations (6.F): `domain/invitations.py`. Token = 32-byte urlsafe, stored plaintext (single-use, ≤90d, grants membership not PHI). TTL clamp [1h, 7d, 90d]. Partial unique `(org, email) WHERE pending` — admin revoke/accept frees slot. Sole-owner / sole-admin demotion + self-demotion blocked. `has_role_at_least(role, "admin")` gates ACCESS; actor_role ≥ target_role gates GRANTING (use `_can_grant_role` on invite + role-change).
- Gotcha: `get_current_user`-computed flags (e.g. `is_org_admin`) go stale for the rest of a request after the handler mutates `active_org_id` / role. Post-mutation routing must use storage truth, not the dict flag. Bitten by `/invite/{token}/accept`.

### Delivery (Phase 9)
- Module layout: `delivery/base.py` (Channel Protocol + `DeliveryReceipt`/`Error` + `ChannelDisabledError`), `delivery/registry.py` (factory reads env at call-time so flips don't need restart), `delivery/channels/{email,fax}.py` (Resend / Documo), `delivery/dispatcher.py` (lifespan asyncio task), `webhook_verifiers/{svix,documo}.py`.
- `deliveries` denormalizes scope from parent (admin list without join); `idempotency_key` UNIQUE partial-index for webhook replay dedup; `packet_artifact` JSON late-binds (dispatcher renders at send, not enqueue). `async_limiter()` caps concurrency (default 5). `asyncio.shield` lets current work finish on SIGTERM cancel. `DOCSTATS_SKIP_DELIVERY_DISPATCHER=1` disables.
- Exponential backoff (9.E): `_backoff_seconds(retry_count)` from `(10, 30, 120, 600, 3600)` ±15% jitter. `_should_skip_for_backoff` checks at pickup (no stored `next_retry_at` column). `DELIVERY_MAX_RETRIES=5`, `DELIVERY_STUCK_SENDING_SECONDS=120` clamp [30, 3600].
- Sweeper health: thread-safe `SweepStats` + `get_sweep_stats()`. Admin route: `/admin/deliveries/health[.json]`. Multi-worker caveat: each worker has its own sweeper + stats; queue-depth counts from `storage.get_delivery_queue_stats()` are DB-authoritative.
- Admin console: `list_deliveries_for_admin(...)` + `get_delivery_queue_stats(...)` on both backends. Cancel audit: `admin.delivery.cancel` with `previous_status` metadata (distinct from coordinator-initiated `delivery.cancel`).
- Channel conventions: (1) raise `ChannelDisabledError` from `__init__` on missing env; (2) retryable = 429/5xx/timeout/network, fatal = 4xx/malformed; (3) pass `Idempotency-Key` header when set; (4) verify HMAC + record raw payload in `webhook_inbox` BEFORE parsing; (5) terminal rows short-circuit — replayed webhooks don't resurrect closed deliveries; (6) `sending` webhook events are informational only (dispatcher owns `queued→sending`).

### Attachments (Phase 10)
- `storage_files/base.py` (Protocol + `FileRef` + `ALLOWED_MIME_TYPES` + `build_object_path`), `storage_files/mime.py` (pure-Python magic-byte sniff, no libmagic — PDF/JPEG/PNG/TIFF/DOCX allow-list), `memory_store.py` (module-level singleton for tests), `supabase_store.py` (sync ops in executor), `factory.py::get_file_backend()`.
- Feature flag: `ATTACHMENT_UPLOAD_ENABLED`. With flag off, every route returns 404. Bucket setup: private Supabase bucket (default `attachments`, overrideable via `SUPABASE_STORAGE_BUCKET`), 50MB limit, NO bucket-level MIME config (app enforces narrower). Service role bypasses RLS. Requires BAA.
- Route contract: POST multipart → sniff MIME (never trust client) → scan (10.B) → insert placeholder row → `file_backend.put()` → update with `storage_ref`. Rollback on `StorageFileError`. GET redirects (302) to 15-minute signed URL. DELETE wipes both row + object (bucket delete best-effort — orphan cleanup in retention sweep).
- Object paths denormalize scope: `{org-<id>|user-<id>}/{referral_id}/{attachment_id}.{ext}`. `MAX_UPLOAD_BYTES=50MB` via `Content-Length` first (pre-spool, 413), then post-read defense. `UploadFile.read(MAX)` does NOT cap — Starlette has already spooled the full body.
- Virus scan (10.B): `storage_files/scanner.py` Protocol + `scanners/cloudmersive.py` (POST `/virus/scan/file`, camelCase `inputFile` NOT `input_file`) + `scanners/noop.py` + `scanner_factory.py`. `VIRUS_SCAN_REQUIRED=1` fail-closed (outage → 502, audit `attachment.scan_unavailable`); unset/0 permissive (dev). Infected verdict always rejects 422 + audit `attachment.scan_rejected`. Cloudmersive 401/429 → `ScannerUnavailable` (transient); missing `CleanResult` treated as scanner-broken.
- Retention (10.C): lifespan sweep (`ATTACHMENT_RETENTION_INTERVAL_SECONDS`, default 86400, clamp [60, 604800]; `DOCSTATS_SKIP_ATTACHMENT_RETENTION=1` disables). Per-org `attachment_retention_days` (default 2555 ≈ 7yr, clamp [30, 10950]). `list_attachments_expired(cutoff, scope_organization_id|scope_user_id, limit)` REQUIRES exactly one scope — raises `ValueError` otherwise (guards against broken callers). Batched 500/tenant, up to 10 batches/sweep/tenant (one tenant can't starve peers). Audit action: `attachment.purged` (no actor_user_id, metadata `{reason: "retention"}`).
- Packet embedding (10.D): `exports/pdf.py::fetch_attachment_pdfs(storage, scope, referral, file_backend)` filters by `.pdf` suffix on `storage_ref` (authoritative — derived from sniffed MIME). `ARTIFACT_ATTACHMENT_PDFS="attachment_pdfs"` is a pseudo-artifact — valid only inside `?include=`, never as `?artifact=`. `delivery/packet_builder.py::build_delivery_packet` is the dispatcher path; `_RENDERERS` + `_fetch_extra()` + `_DEFAULT_INCLUDE` must stay in sync with `routes/exports.py`. Missing blobs logged + skipped (one orphan doesn't fail the packet).

### Lifespan background tasks (shared pattern)
Used by `delivery.dispatcher` + `storage_files.retention`: (1) `DOCSTATS_SKIP_<NAME>=1` env disables; (2) conftest sets skip-flag by default; (3) thread-safe `*Stats` dataclass + `get_*_stats()` for admin health; (4) `asyncio.wait_for(stop_event.wait(), timeout=interval)` loop + `finally: _set_running(False)`; (5) lifespan creates task + `asyncio.wait_for(task, timeout=15)` on shutdown.

### API v2 / interop (Phase 8)
- `routes/api_v2.py`: `GET /api/v2/referrals/{id}`, `GET /api/v2/patients/{id}` (content-negotiated: Accept substring `fhir+json` → FHIR; `*/*` → plain JSON, regression-pinned), `POST /api/v2/webhooks/inbound`. Every response carries `X-Docstats-Api-Version: 2`. FHIR errors emit `OperationOutcome`; plain errors `{code, detail}`.
- **Critical**: API routes use `require_user_api` + `require_phi_consent_api` — these raise `HTTPException(401/403)` JSON. Plain `require_user` / `require_phi_consent` raise `AuthRequiredException` which 303-redirects to `/auth/login` (fatal for machine consumers). Regression-pinned by `test_referral_unauthenticated_returns_401_json_not_redirect`.
- Webhook inbox: HMAC-signed (`sha256(f"{X-Timestamp}.{body}")`, accepts `sha256=<hex>` or bare hex). `WEBHOOK_INBOX_SECRET` unset → 503 (distinct from 401). ±5min replay window. 256KB cap (Content-Length first, then post-read; Postgres CHECK `octet_length(payload_json::text) <= 262144` at DB layer too). Headers filtered to 5-name allowlist (`content-type`, `user-agent`, `x-signature`, `x-timestamp`, `x-source`). No handlers yet — Phase 11 consumes.

### Audit log
- `domain/audit.py`: `AuditEvent` + `record(storage, *, action, request=None, ...)` swallows errors (audit failure must never break caller). Action vocabulary: `{entity}.{verb}` (e.g. `user.login`, `provider.save`). Append-only by contract; FKs `ON DELETE SET NULL` so rows survive user deletion.
- Prefer `ON DELETE SET NULL` over `CASCADE` on audit/log/immutable-history tables. `CASCADE` only for derived per-user data (saved_providers).
- New action strings: append to `_KNOWN_AUDIT_ACTIONS` in `routes/admin.py` (alphabetical) for datalist autocomplete. Unlisted actions still work; just undiscoverable.
- IP/UA caps: `validators.py` `IP_MAX_LENGTH=45`, `USER_AGENT_MAX_LENGTH=500`. Truncate at the storage boundary.
- **Audit-before-delete**: `audit.record(action="user.account_deleted")` must fire BEFORE `delete_user()` — actor_user_id FK must still exist. Omit `entity_type`/`entity_id` entirely: plain-text entity_id would survive deletion and contradict anonymization; actor_user_id SET NULL is the correct surviving identifier.
- **`list_audit_events` AND semantics**: `actor_user_id` + `scope_user_id` are AND-filtered. For OR (events where user was actor OR events scoped to their data): two separate calls + deduplicate by `ev.id`.

### Sessions / auth / PHI consent
- `domain/sessions.py`: server-side sessions, URL-safe 32-byte token. Cookie carries `user_id` + `session_id`. `get_current_user` rejects revoked/expired rows + clears cookie. `_begin_session` rotates on every login/signup/OAuth (revokes prior) + `request.session.clear()` before seeding (prevents cross-user flag leak). Legacy cookies (pre-session) grandfathered one request. Session lookup fails CLOSED.
- `last_seen_at` touched only when older than `_TOUCH_MIN_INTERVAL` (5min).
- `sessions.user_id` uses `ON DELETE CASCADE` — sessions are derived access, not evidence.
- PHI consent: 4 columns on `users` (`phi_consent_version`/`at`/`ip`/`user_agent`) independent from general ToS. `src/docstats/phi.py` exposes `CURRENT_PHI_CONSENT_VERSION` + `require_phi_consent` dep (raises `PhiConsentRequiredException` extending `AuthRequiredException`). First consumer: patients routes (2.A). Bumping version forces re-accept at next PHI-route hit, NOT next login.
- OAuth: `oauth.py` GitHub helpers; `routes/auth.py` wires GitHub OAuth App (callback `https://referme.help/auth/github/callback`). `SESSION_SECRET_KEY` unset → random (dev-only fallback, sessions don't survive restart).
- `passlib[bcrypt]` is incompatible with `bcrypt>=4.0.0` — pin `bcrypt>=3.2.0,<4.0.0`.
- **Revoke session before `delete_user`**: clear `request.session` + call `storage.revoke_session()` BEFORE `delete_user()`. Sessions CASCADE-delete with the user row — after deletion there's nothing left to revoke, and the explicit revoke prevents any race on the same connection.
- Auth tests: `app.dependency_overrides[get_current_user] = lambda: fake_user_dict` — `require_user` inherits automatically.

### NPPES / enrichment / scoring
- `client.py` is sync (`httpx.Client`) — web.py must use `async_search()`/`async_lookup()` (executor-wrapped). CLI uses sync directly.
- NPPES endpoint: `https://npiregistry.cms.hhs.gov/api/?version=2.1`. Can't combine NPI-1 (first/last) with NPI-2 (org_name). Returns names UPPERCASE, phones unformatted, postal codes raw. No middle_name search. Name search matches `other_names` — prefix-filter by current name when relevance matters. No documented rate limits but 500s under load — `client.py` retries 3x backoff.
- `taxonomies.py`: 883 NUCC entries for client-side specialty autocomplete.
- `http_retry.py::request_with_retry()` — exponential backoff (`backoff_base=2.0` → 1s/2s/4s; `1.0` silently degrades to constant). Honors integer `Retry-After` (HTTP-date not supported). On exhaustion, chains `__cause__`.
- Env knobs (read at call-time): `DOCSTATS_HTTP_TIMEOUT` (30s), `DOCSTATS_HTTP_MAX_RETRIES` (3), `DOCSTATS_HTTP_CONCURRENCY` (5, for `async_limiter()`).
- Enrichment: `enrichment.py` orchestrator + `EnrichmentCache` (same SQLite, source-aware keys, per-source TTL: OIG 30d, Medicare 7d, Open Payments 30d). Clients: `oig_client.py` (LEIE monthly CSV, NPI index; utf-8-sig for BOM), `cms_client.py` (DKAN `mj5m-pzi6`/`27ea-46a8`), `open_payments_client.py` (2024→2023 fallback). DKAN pattern: `POST {base}/api/1/datastore/query/{id}/0` with `{"conditions": [{"property": "npi", "value": "<npi>", "operator": "="}]}`. Retry tests: patch `client._http.request` + `docstats.http_retry.time.sleep`.
- Detail page lazy-loads via htmx `hx-get="/provider/{npi}/enrichment"`.
- Scoring (`scoring.py`): ranked by Web UI (`routes/search.py`) + CLI (`services.py`). Geo tiers (≤15mi +25, ≤30mi +20, ≤60mi +15, ≤120mi +10), state-match fallback +8. OIG excluded −100, Medicare enrolled +10. In smart-search, `search_kwargs` + `SearchQuery` built from `interp` — explicit form params (`specialty`/`city`/`state`/`zip`) must be injected separately. `rank_results()` must receive `SearchQuery` built from winning `interp` (first_name/last_name/organization_name/taxonomy_description) in smart path.
