## Git / PRs / workflow

- **Don't use `gh pr checks --watch`** — streams indefinitely. Poll: `until ! gh pr checks N --repo ringo380/docstats | grep -q pending; do sleep 15; done`. For blocking-only (skip Continuous AI): `... 2>&1 | grep -E "^Test .*pending"`.
- **Clean squash commits**: always pass `--subject` + `--body` (HEREDOC) to `gh pr merge <N> --squash --delete-branch`. Without them, gh concatenates every commit title into a noisy default message.
- **`--delete-branch`** deletes remote but `origin/<branch>` ref not pruned locally. `git remote prune origin` after. Local branch needs `git branch -d <name>` separately.
- **After squash-merge of multi-commit branch**, local main has unsquashed originals — `git reset --hard origin/main`.
- **Stacked PRs auto-close when base squash-merges with `--delete-branch`**; GitHub refuses to reopen. Workaround: rebase onto new main locally (`git rebase --onto origin/main <old-base> <stacked>`), force-push or new branch, fresh PR. Prefer branching off `main` from the start.
- **Codex-generated PRs** (branch prefix `codex/...`) land as draft. Always `gh pr ready <N>` before `gh pr merge`.
- **`gh pr merge`** for this repo is allow-listed via user-level rule `Bash(gh pr merge * --repo ringo380/docstats:*)` in `~/.claude/settings.json`. `git push origin main` still sandbox-blocked.
- **SSH agent drops** (1Password lock, keychain re-prompt) silently break `git pull`/`fetch` while `git push https://... -c credential.helper='!gh auth git-credential'` still works. Symptom: branch off local main missing last-merged PR files. Recovery: `git fetch https://github.com/ringo380/docstats.git main:refs/remotes/origin/main` then rebase. Always re-verify `git log --oneline -1 origin/main` after a merge when SSH has been flaky.
- **Plan lifecycle**: keep multi-phase plans in `.claude/plans/` while ANY sub-phase incomplete; archive only when entire plan done. Shipping Phase 2 of 16 does NOT archive.
- **No AI attribution anywhere** (commits, PRs, docs, code review comments). Never add `Co-Authored-By: Claude` or "Generated with Claude Code". Never commit `.claude/`, `CLAUDE.md`, `memory/`. Always verify `.gitignore` excludes them.
- **Ad-hoc Supabase SELECTs**: same Management-API endpoint as migrations. `curl -sS -X POST "https://api.supabase.com/v1/projects/uhnymifvdauzlmaogjfj/database/query" -H "Authorization: Bearer $SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN" -H "Content-Type: application/json" --data '{"query": "SELECT ..."}'`.

